column5: We are headed to Gullrock in one week. With the late spring, I am curious if we will be fishing pre-spawn walleyes, or post spawn. Or maybe right in the middle of the spawn. Anyone heard of water temperatures up that way? Thanks, Pat T
Was on Cliff Lake other day and water temps there were 35-45 f if that helps water up nor√æh probably the same or cooler.will see how many eggs there are on Sunday when I take party out on Lac Suel.
Thats quite a temperature spread. 35-45 I would bet that they are spawning.
